Igor,

I’ve just started to look at the new InChI code and I came across the following on lines 2455 to 2470 in runichi3.c:

        for (i=0; i<nrings; i++)*;*

        {

            int erank, max_erank = 0;

            for (k=0; k<nat; k++)

            {

                if ( aprops[k].ring_num == i )

                {

                    erank = erank_rule2[ at[k].el_number ];

                    if ( erank > max_erank )

                        max_erank = erank;

                }

            }

            for (k=0; k<nat; k++)

                if ( aprops[k].ring_num == i )

                    aprops[k].ring_erank = max_erank;

        }

If I’m reading this code correctly it looks like the semicolon at the end of the first line means that the remaining code only gets executed once (with i = nrings). Is the semicolon a typo?

Peter

